{
  "_comment": "SG-lite (SURNAME-GAZETTEER-DESIGN.md §2.2): hand-written collision list — surnames that are also common Polish nouns (fauna, flora, objects, professions, calendar, adjectival derivatives of common stems), the class the NER model reads as a noun and stays silent on. NOT a general surname list (§1 niecel); grown from the leak register, one entry + test per new leak. SEED (~33 entries, unchanged): initial coverage of the measured holdout leaks (Osioł, Wrona, Pszczoła, Dzięcioł, Głowacka) plus the obvious members of the same collision families. EXTENSION PASS (2026-07, +122 entries, 155 total): broadened fauna/flora/przedmioty-zawody/kalendarz coverage per the same collision-class criterion, added in batches with the consistency + matcher test suites green after each. Every added entry is believed to be a real Polish surname from general onomastic knowledge, NOT cross-checked against the PESEL dataset (no dataset access in this pass) — several lower-confidence entries carry a deliberately low `freq` bucket (1) as an honest flag; masculine surnames derived from inanimate common nouns (trees, tools) are declined with the personal/virile genitive -a (e.g. Dąb→Dęba, not Dębu), the standard convention for Polish surnames regardless of the source noun's grammatical animacy. The full 300-500 entry list, final slotOnly membership and freq calibration remain an EDITORIAL decision for Alan (O-SG-4) — this pass does not close that review, it is input to it. `freq` is the log10 bearer-count bucket per the PESEL surname dataset (dane.gov.pl 1681, CC0 1.0 — confirmed at source in W1-W3-MORPHOLOGY-DESIGN.md §1.2.2); ALL buckets (seed and extension) are best-effort estimates TO BE VERIFIED against the dataset at the O-SG-4 review. Forms are hand-written declensions (incl. stem alternations like Kozioł→Kozła, Orzeł→Orła, Sokół→Sokoła, Wąż→Węża); they are NOT copied from SGJP, so no BSD-2 material enters the repo (design §2.2 pkt 2). firstNames: hand-written nominative seed for slot S1 — the compiled PESEL top-1500 import is a separate open decision (O-SG-2). titles/functionPhrases: closed slot-signal lists for S3/S5 (§2.2 pkt 6).",
  "entityGroup": "PERSON_NAME",
